You should never go to a restaurant and leave in tears. This place absolutely ruined my day. I made an order for pickup on DoorDash. When I got there I was ignored for awhile sitting at the bar. I have to get the bartender’s attention to tell him I’m there to pick up the order. I have the receipt on my phone, and as he is quickly walking by, just says we don’t have bean burritos anymore. Then he brings me the 1 page paper menu stating the menu changed, and I’ll have to pay more for a different item. I prepaid already online and showed him a picture of what I ordered. It is the meal which has 2 bean and cheese burritos with a side of rice and beans. So, he says okay, we’ll make you a bean burrito. I was expecting to get what I actually ordered, but what I got was just 1 bean burrito, no cheese, no rice & beans. So by the way, after I’m sitting there for a while, the guy never mentioned they don’t have the tamales that I paid $13 for. Like, I was just out of luck. I had to have an argument with the guy and say they have to give me something since I’ve already been charged. So I tell him I’ll take tacos instead. Never mind those were a lower priced item. They never offered me any compensation. I just want to leave and never return at this point so I’m not going argue about it. If I had not kept on them, I’m guessing they would have given me nothing. So, I also ordered queso dip and a guacamole. Like after I’m sitting there a half hour (after the original order was supposed to be ready) the guy comes out and says they don’t have any queso. At this point I’m ready to cry. He offers me double guacamole. I said okay. He then says to me, “This is not our fault.” Um, yes, this is the restaurant’s fault. They need to either fix their menu online or withdraw themselves from online ordering services until they can correct it. Just to add insult to injury, they never asked me if I wanted a drink, not even water, while I waited for a half hour during this whole debacle. I can’t even eat the food now. I’m afraid of what they might have done to it. As I left, I was singing Kelly Clarkson’s ‘Never Again’ in my head.  I wished I would have just stayed home. This is officially my worst restaurant experience of all time.

This place has gone through many changes through the years, but the latest changes have been the worst. They've reduce the size of the menu from five pages to two. They've changed suppliers and have whittled everything down to basic food, there used to be texture, flavor and choices here but my recent experience doesn't make me want to return even though my family have been going here for the better part of over 30 years.  When I was there earlier tonight the queso had a taste of sweat and was unenjoyable, previously they used different spices and flavors to make it something that was impossible not to eat. I followed that up with a fajita steak burrito, now I understand that sauces can be put on a burrito but when you drench it in sauce to the point where I cannot pick it up and eat it like it's meant to be eaten, I'm not happy. I had to use a fork and knife on a burrito that had rubbery steak, their previous owner would use steak that would be marinated at least and that did not feel like I was chewing a rubber band. I want this place to be better, I came here ever since I was a child but now I think those memories are where I'll visit this place in the future.  Today it's a one star restaurant, I gave it one extra for the memories and how it used to be. Save your money and go to Chipotle.  ----Update---- 10/18/19 Visiting here for another family function. It's terrible, not much has changed from what what stated above but when you pay $20 for a steak and half of it is pure fat mixed with real meat it makes you think they're serving meat glue steaks. It's obvious that they've decided to use the cheapest food suppliers rather than quality suppliers.  Don't come here unless you want to waste your money on trash.

Worst restaurant experience in my life. My husband and I stopped by this place a few months ago one Sunday afternoon.... during that time period after the lunch crowd but before the dinner crowd. We weren't quite ready but what ever, we where hungry so not a huge deal. I didnt realize something was off until she came back immediately after dropping off our order at kitchen with our check. What?!?  We hadn't even received our drinks yet and the waitress was already bring out our bill telling us that we can pay when we are ready. I with a hint of naivete responded by telling her that we had not yet received our order. The waitress then rolled her eyes, aggressively snatched the bill up off the table, and walked away. That was the last time we saw her until we flagged her down for our bill when we were done. No chips and salsa, no water refills, no 2nd round of drinks, no periodic check ups. We could not have felt more unwelcomed. The waitress either wanted to rush us through our meal & out the door because we were gay OR more likely, she was not so discreetly trying to suggest that we needed to pre-pay for our food...possibly because I am African American. Either way, the service was awful, our experience was awful, & I am never going back.

If I can give this place less than 1 star trust me, I would, in a heartbeat too! This place is DISGUSTING to say the very very least. I’ve never at here and I never will (I will explain why, just bear with me it’s gunna be a long story. SO WORTH READING EVERYTHING THOUGH) , PLEASE DO NOT EAT HERE.  Like I said I’ve never ate here. The reason I found out this place is so disgusting is bc I worked there! I desperately needed a job one summer (at the time I was 19) so I just walked in and politely asked if they were hiring. The manager, which is like a muscular Mexican guy (somewhere in his 40s) said he could definitely use me. He then told me to come back tmrw at 8am.  The day has come, it’s a Monday and I show up. The first thing he has me do is listen to another guy around my age (his name is johnathan) because he was gunna show me how to open the restaurant. I was hired as a dishwasher/busser. The guy (johnathan) starts telling me we just have to pick the chairs up and sweep and mop the whole restaurant. Immediately as I take my first step on the floor I feel that it’s EXTREMELY sticky. Mind you, I’ve worked at other restaurants before so I thought it’d be like any other. NO. No other restaurant I’ve ever worked at has had a sticky floor from all the food that falls on the floor. I desperately needed a job so I tough it out. Then probably I swear to god 5 mins into me sweeping I sweep up 2 HUGE ROACHES from under the table. I never worked at a restaurant with roaches that are actually IN and ON the diner floor. Even the broom and mop they gave me to use felt so sticky greasy and was full of pieces of food ON THE HANDLE, not the broom or the mop itself BUT THE HANDLE. Then it probably took me about 20 mins to sweep. And I kid you not within those 20 mins I swept up AT LEAST 10 roaches!! YES, I SAID TEN ROACH, ONLY WHILE I SWEPT. After I was done by that every step  I took it with so much paranoia bc I was scared I would step on a roach(which I did twice).  Now I’m supposed to mop I start mopping and I realize it doesn’t matter if you kill one or two bc they will just multiply. While I mopped the whole restaurant I killed I’d say about another 8 HUGE ROACHES. If I had to take a guess I would say every roach I found was at least anywhere from 1 whole in to maybe 1 inch and a half. I promise you guys I wanted to take my phone out and record so bad but the only reason I didn’t was bc I was so disgusted to even grab my phone with the same hands I was grabbing the mop with.  After I was done with this I was probably an hour into the job.  Then johnathan takes me to the storage room to stock up for the morning. The storage room is in a whole other building. We go up the stairs and in the storage room the room is so dirty it honestly looks like it’s never ever been cleaned. AND on top of that the room was as hot as outside! This was all around July of 2018. Very few of the items are kept in a fridge/freezer. The only things kept cool are stuff like dairy products. The tomatoes, onions, vegetables and eggs are just left out in a small room which is just as hot as outside. He tells me to take some tomatoe boxes to the kitchen. I’m pickup tomatoe boxes that are stacked maybe a bit shorter than me (I’m 5’8”). Once I get to probably the third to last box I can now see the floor. And on the floor corner which is I’d say 2-3 feet from where the boxes where piled I see a DEAD RAT ON A RAT TRAP. YES!! I kid you not there was a dead rat laying around all the produce.  After I saw that I could not take it anymore. ABSOLUTELY NO money is enough to have me work under those conditions. I walked out without telling anyone anything probably less than two hours into my first ever shift. Never been there since.  The reason I wrote this review is to inform the public on what really goes on there. People literally eat where roaches live and rats die. For any type of food business that is UNACCEPTABLE. Please guys do not go here. I do not know how this place is still running! This place needs to be shut down and sanitized ASAP!

We opted for 2 cuervo margaritas, beef tacos served with refried beans and rice, and (from the specials) shrimp chimichangas serviced with rice, sour cream and salad.  Service was friendly and prompt. Taste was excellent - best Mexican meal we've had (having never visited actual Mexico...). Quantity was large, we left feeling satisfied.  We thought this was excellent value for money ($55 for the above).

The decor is what you would expect, the people working there just move about delivering drinks and food without any sign of life. I ordered queso fundido and the cheese was stringy and not dip-able at all. SO ordered the tacos which from report were good, but they looked like I could have made them at home. The beans looked dried out and the rice from a box. I guess the margaritas are good but we didn't have them. I typically check reviews before I eat anyplace and considering the location I thought this must be good. I was wrong. Please save yourself and go elsewhere.

I would rate the drinks a 2 out of 10  Food: I ordered the tacos racheros (steak) and the food was delivered rather quickly but it left nothing to be desired. I have had tacos that have had more flavor from a street corner. I also had my daughter and niece with me who order queso and quamole which they stated "was nasty". I would rate the food a 2 out of 10.  My opinion: skip this restaurant if you are looking to experience  excellent food choices or you will be disappointed unless you have a palette that does not require well seasoned food with pride and love in the recipe.
